------Nov 12  2024------

Using all Y chr assemblies + HG002 [samtools faidx GCF_009914755.1_T2T-CHM13v2.0_genomic.fna.gz NC_060948.1 > HG002.fasta]

first download gene ID's from google sheet / get sequence with script get_human_gene.py
then use scrpt align_43.py to align all gene copies to the assemblies, collect their location (multiple
copies can map to one location), get the longest sequence from a given location, extract ORF from location


for RBMY one of the alignements spanned two copies. With the align_43 workflow this was considered as one gene copy,
- added checking of gene length 


running blast with "blast_results.py" script

`python blast_results.py > alignments_v3/all_genes.blast.txt`

Results copies to https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/15kmM8qLrhzd9FARj7I4bgl-jjqCZD3Wbeq7-PXU7now/edit?gid=453161453#gid=453161453


